“appointed  date”  has  the  same  meaning  as  is  assigned  to  that
expression  in  the  Intellectual  Property  Corporation  of  Malaysia
Act  2002  [Act  617];

“Assistant Registrar” means the person appointed or deemed to
have been appointed to be an Assistant Registrar under subsection
8(2)  or  (3);

“competent authority” means any government or statutory body
carrying  out  the  functions  of,  on  behalf  of,  or  sanctioned  by,  the
Government;

“Corporation”  means  the  Intellectual  Property  Corporation  of
Malaysia  established  under  the  Intellectual  Property  Corporation
of  Malaysia  Act  2002;

“Deputy  Registrar”  means  the  person  appointed  or  deemed  to
have  been  appointed  to  be  a  Deputy  Registrar  under  subsection
8(2)  or  (3);

“Paris Convention” means the Paris Convention for the Protection
of  Industrial  Property  of  20  March  1883,  as  revised  or  amended
from  time  to  time;

“protectable  geographical  indication”  means  a  geographical
indication  which  does  not  fall  within  any  of  the  categories  of
geographical  indications  specified  in  section  4;

“registered proprietor”, in relation to a geographical indication,
means  the  person  for  the  time  being  entered  in  the  Register  as
proprietor  of  the  geographical  indication;

(a) geographical  indications  that  do  not  correspond  to  the
meaning of “geographical indication” as defined in section
2;

(b) any  use  in  the  course  of  trade  which  constitutes  an  act
of unfair competition within the meaning of Article 10bis
of  the  Paris  Convention  as  set  out  in  the  Schedule;

(a) the  name,  address  and  nationality  of  the  natural  person
or legal entity filing the application, and the capacity in
which  the  applicant  is  applying  for  registration;

(2) In  particular  and  without  prejudice  to  the  generality  of
subsection  (1),  regulations  made  under  this  section  may  provide
for  all  or  any  of  the  following:

(d) to  regulate  the  keeping  of  the  Register  and  to  prescribe
its form and contents; and to prescribe the conditions and
fees  for  making  any  extracts  of  the  Register;

(f) for  doing  anything  required  to  be  done  in  connection
with any proceedings or other matters before the Registrar
or  the  Central  Geographical  Indications  Office;

all acts of such a nature as to create confusion by any means whatever
with  the  establishment,  the  goods,  or  the  industrial  or  commercial
activities,  of  a  competitor;

